      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and grate<strong> half </strong>your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining onion</strong> into wedges</p><p>Add your <strong>beef mince </strong>to a bowl with the<strong> grated onion</strong>,<strong> ground coriander</strong>,<strong> half </strong>your <strong>ground cumin </strong>(save the rest for later!) and<strong> </strong>a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Using clean hands, give everything a good mix up until fully combined, then roll the<strong> burger mixture </strong>into 1<strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>meatball per person and press down with your hands to form a patty – this is your <strong>beef kofta patty</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
