    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> and <strong>parsley</strong> roughly, including the stalks and cut your <strong>lemon[s]</strong> in half</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped chilli</strong> (not a fan of spice? Just add a little!), <strong>chopped parsley </strong>and <strong>coriander</strong> to a <strong>pestle & mortar</strong> with a small pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and grind to a paste</p><p>Add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong>,<strong> </strong>the<strong> </strong>juice of the<strong> lemon[s]</strong> and the <strong>remaining ground cumin</strong> and stir it all together – this is your <strong>zhoug</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
